==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hie
<hw>Hie</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Hied</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>hien</ets>,
<ets>hihen</ets>, <ets>highen</ets>, AS. <ets>higian</ets> to hasten,
strive; cf. L. <ets>ciere</ets> to put in motion, call upon, rouse, Gr.
<?/ to go, E. <ets>cite</ets>.]</ety> <def>To hasten; to go in haste; --
also often with the reciprocal pronoun.</def> <mark>[Rare, except in
poetry]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧My husband <xex>hies</xex> him home.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The youth, returning to his mistress, <qex>hies</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hie</ent>⟦br⟧

